snippet.textDisplay:
Reinterpreting the Lyrics by chatgpt

Chokh puraavo, Maati rangaavo, Aaj mere piya ghar aavenge
In this context, "piya" (beloved) symbolizes his father, whose spirit is now returning to the divine home. The act of "beautifying the eyes" and "coloring the earth" becomes a way of honoring his father’s memory and celebrating his journey to eternal peace.

Khabar sunaau jo, Khushi reh bataau jo, Aaj mere piya ghar aavenge
The singer shares the bittersweet news of his father's passing, expressing both sorrow and acceptance, recognizing this as a sacred transition.

Meri sakhi mangal gaau ree, Dharti ambar sajaao ree
"O friends, sing auspicious songs, adorn the earth and the sky." This reflects the rituals performed for a departed soul, invoking blessings and celebrating the life lived, as per spiritual traditions.

Utregi aaj mere pi ki sawaari, Har koi kaajal laau ree, Moi kaala teeka lagaao ree
The "procession" of his father’s spirit signifies the ceremonial departure of the soul. The protective rituals symbolize prayers for a safe journey to the afterlife.

Unki chat se dikhu mee re pyaare, Lachhmi ji vaaro, Nazar utaaro
The reference to seeing his father from above could symbolize his father's presence watching over him. Invoking Goddess Lakshmi and warding off the evil eye reflects a spiritual plea for peace and divine blessings for the departed soul.

Rang se rang mile, Nai nai dhang khile, Khushi aaj ghar mere daale hai dhera
This line celebrates his father's legacy and the joy he brought to the family, blending the sorrow of loss with gratitude for his life.

Peehu peehu papiha rate, Kuhu kuhu koyal jape, Aangan aagan hai pariyon ne ghera
The birds and celestial beings symbolize a harmonious send-off, as if nature itself participates in honoring his father.

Anhat naat, Bajaao sab milat, Aaj mere piya ghar aavenge
The "divine music" signifies the spiritual elevation of his father's soul. It’s a collective call to celebrate a life that is now united with the divine.
